; Regression test for issue #761: Make uncommoditized amounts behave like
; commoditized ones (BZ#761)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/761
;
; When the "D" directive specifies a default commodity format without a
; commodity symbol (e.g. "D 1.000,00"), the thousands separator and
; decimal-comma style should be applied to subsequent bare (uncommoditized)
; amounts so that they display with the same format.
;
; Before the fix, the observed numeric format of a bare D amount was
; discarded because the parsed amount had no commodity to attach the
; style to; bare posting amounts printed without separators.

D 1.000,00

2012-03-29 * foo
    foo:bar    123.456,78
    bar:foo

2024/01/02 another
    foo:bar    5.000,99
    bar:foo

2024/01/03 negative
    foo:bar    -999,75
    bar:foo

; Balance shows all bare amounts in European format.
test bal
         -127.458,02  bar:foo
          127.458,02  foo:bar
--------------------
                   0
end test

; Register view shows each bare amount in European format.
test reg
12-Mar-29 foo                   foo:bar                  123.456,78   123.456,78
                                bar:foo                 -123.456,78            0
24-Jan-02 another               foo:bar                    5.000,99     5.000,99
                                bar:foo                   -5.000,99            0
24-Jan-03 negative              foo:bar                     -999,75      -999,75
                                bar:foo                      999,75            0
end test
